# Codacy CLI generates default tools-configs/ locally; most are noise
# we don't want to commit.  However, bandit.yaml is referenced from
# /.codacy.yml (config_file:) and the Codacy SaaS scanner reads it
# from the checked-in repo — without it, B101 (assert_used) floods
# the dashboard with hundreds of alerts from tests/.  Ignore the dir,
# then un-ignore the one file we need to track.
tools-configs/*
!tools-configs/bandit.yaml
cli-config.yaml
codacy.yaml
logs/
